Notebook Schema¶

  1. Get stocks data from yfinance package for Python, for Tesla, Bitcoin and Dogecoin;
  2. Visualize data - create line plots for each feature (close price and returns - simple and log) for each ticker;
  3. Don't forget to preprocess data:
    • create log and simple returns variables;
    • rescale Close Price for each ticker of interest;
    • label data for classification:
      • if return > 0 then label = 1
      • if return 0 then label = 0

In [3]:
# get data on this ticker
TSLA = yf.Ticker(tickerTSLA)
BTC = yf.Ticker(tickerBTC)
DOGE = yf.Ticker(tickerDOGE)

# get the historical prices for those two tickers
df_TSLA = TSLA.history(period='1d', start='2010-6-29', end='2023-5-13')
df_BTC = BTC.history(period='1d', start='2014-9-17', end='2023-5-13')
df_DOGE = DOGE.history(period='1d', start='2017-11-9', end='2023-5-13')

Create new features:¶

  • simple return and log return for Tesla, Dogecoin and Bitcoin

    Simple return: $R_t=\frac{P_t - P_{t-1}}{P_{t-1}}$

    Log-return: $r_t = \log\left(\frac{P_t}{P_{t-1}}\right)=\log{P_t}-\log{P_{t-1}}$

  • close price rescaled

    Rescaled Close Price: $ClosePrice_{res}=\frac{P_t - min(P_{t})}{max(P_{t}) - min(P_{t})}$

In [7]:
DOGE = df_DOGE[['Date', 'Close', 'Volume']]
DOGE['Close_Doge'] = DOGE['Close']
DOGE['Volume_Doge'] = DOGE['Volume']
DOGE['simple_return_Doge'] = DOGE['Close_Doge'].pct_change().dropna()
DOGE['log_return_Doge'] = np.log(1+DOGE['simple_return_Doge'])

max_DOGE = DOGE['Close_Doge'].max()
min_DOGE = DOGE['Close_Doge'].min()
DOGE['Close_Doge_Rescaled'] = (DOGE['Close_Doge'] - min_DOGE)/(max_DOGE - min_DOGE)

max_DOGE_v = DOGE['Volume_Doge'].max()
min_DOGE_v = DOGE['Volume_Doge'].min()
DOGE['Volume_Doge_Rescaled'] = (DOGE['Volume_Doge'] - min_DOGE_v)/(max_DOGE_v - min_DOGE_v)

DOGE.drop(['Close', 'Volume'], axis=1, inplace=True)
